[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - The test’s `ObjectOutputStream.replaceObject` replaced the first encoded `byte[]` with `EncodedPublicKey`.
[assistant] - `EncodedPublicKey` itself stored that same `byte[]` as a field.
[assistant] - Java serialization reused the already-replaced handle for that `byte[]`, so deserialization tried to assign an `EncodedPublicKey` object into a `byte[]` field, causing the `ClassCastException`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
